HEADWORD: foghorn
<hw>fog"horn</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A horn that emits a loud
low-pitched sound, used on ships navigating in a fog, to warn other
ships of their presence.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fog signal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

